The paper deals with image registration using a pre-trained deep neural network as a feature extractor, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a pre-trained network for a new task also falls under the category of transfer learning, which is a popular research area in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of uncertainty calculation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The technique is applied to multi-modal images, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of real-time registration, which could involve the use of neural networks for efficient computation, making it relevant to the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
